natural problem:
Find all complex numbers $z$ such that
\begin{align*}
\left| \frac{z - 4}{z - 8} \right| &= 1, \\
\left| \frac{z - 12}{z - 8i} \right| &= \frac{5}{3}.
\end{align*}Enter all the solutions, separated by commas.
natural solution: Let $z = x + yi,$ where $x$ and $y$ are real numbers.
From the equation $\left| \frac{z - 4}{z - 8} \right| = 1,$ $|z - 4| = |z - 8|.$  Then \[|x + yi - 4| = |x + yi - 8|,\]so $(x - 4)^2 + y^2 = (x - 8)^2 + y^2.$  This simplifies to $x = 6.$

From the equation $\left| \frac{z - 12}{z - 8i} \right| = \frac{5}{3},$ $3|z - 12| = 5|z - 8i|.$  Then \[3|6 + yi - 12| = 5|6 + yi - 8i|,\]so $9(36 + y^2) = 25(36 + (y - 8)^2).$  This simplifies to $16y^2 - 400y + 2176 = 0,$ which factors as $16(y - 8)(y - 17) = 0.$  Hence, $y = 8$ or $y = 17.$
